On Wed, 31 Mar 2010, Mike Benthin wrote:

> I have a piece of 1x4 I ground down so it just fits between the top edge of 
> the valve cover and the engine floor above it- to prevent the valve cover 
> from sliding off the head as the bale is pried up. Greasing the area the bale 
> wire rubs on helps also.

a tool I have found to be almost perfect for removing the valve cover bail 
is an old shoemakers "heel lifter" just the right size and shape, can 
often find em in flea markets or at a "Shoe finders" store if looking for 
new mine probably cost $5-10 new, 20 years ago.... $1-2 at a flea market. 
looks a bit like a wide flat curved screwdriver.


Bob
